history.content:
For Spring 2019, students' Phase 1 ends on November 11, 2018 at 11:59:00pm PST.

This means students will not be able to add, drop, swap, change grading option, change unit values until their Phase 2 start date and time begins for Spring 2019.

Students (with some exclusions) will be notified of this deadline and when they may make class adjustments again.

 

New undergraduate students Spring 2019 enrollment begins on November 13, 2018. New undergraduate students will not be notified of Phase 1 ending.

Students can check CalCentral to see when their Phase II appointments begin.
